nt||tu||HT|b|va|4|cs|1|cp|4|fp|3|at|^-{    Thurston Meets the Movie Maker    }
^-|CP||FP||ht|d|cp|8|at|^*B@2Thurston: |cp||at|To start, 2/1 usually has a greater and more accurate way to raise major suit openings. In Standard American or SAYC, 1M-2M can be 3 or 4 trumps, 6-10 HCP and that's too wide a range of support for accurate follow up. In 2/1, we usually add Bergen Raises and use 1M-2M as very specific: 8-10 with exactly 3 trumps.|
PG| ***** 137 ***** |


cp|8|at|

- |cp||at|The Bergen variety I prefer now is Reverse: 3C = a 4 card limit raise, 10-12 and 3D= 7+-10 with 4 trumps (a 4-card constructive raise). You'll note an overlap: at the 10 end" that's to distinguish good 10's from poor.  Aces and Kings = good cards, Queens and Jacks = poor. |
PG| ***** 138 ***** |


cp|8|at|

- |cp||at|So 1S - 3C with Axxx Kxxx Kx xxx(10 HCP) but 1S-3D with Kxxx Qxxx QJx Qx(10 HCP). After the raise, Opener will have a much better idea of when he should head towards game and when he should stop in part score.|
PG| ***** 139 ***** |


cp|8|at|

- |cp||at|The next change focuses on how to try for game after a raise. Opener will usually need a medium hand - 15-17 + to try for game after 1M-2M. And that add is in distributional points after the raise. For example AJxxxx is worth about 2 more points for the 6th trump after supported. In SAYC or standard, the usual way to try for game was to rebid the M -1M-2M 3M? to ask partner if she was min or maximum.|
PG| ***** 140 ***** |


cp|8|at|

- |cp||at|But that ignores the element of fit which is just about always more important - not "how many points partner?" but "where are your points?" In any case, what Opener needs to know is "do the hands fit well?"|
PG| ***** 141 ***** |


cp|8|at|

- |cp||at|What we use to find out is a Help Suit Game Try (HSGT): Opener bids the suit she/he has losers in to ask for help and Responder goes to game with help and stays out with no help. It is easy to distinguish between shortness and helping request. Shortness applies after 1M-2N  and HSGT after 1M-2M.|
PG| ***** 142 ***** |


cp|8|at|

- |cp||at|Remember after 1S-2S we have a trump suit and that's what we're going to playing so bidding a new suit is not looking for a different trump suit - don't be greedy, one fit is enough. For this HSGT to work, we have to have agreed on a major (1M-2M) and have room to say "no help" by going back to 3M. If Help suit is higher ranked - it will only be so after 1H-2H-2S - then 4H with help and 3H with no help.|
PG| ***** 143 ***** |


